issue.title: Model templates refactoring for readability -- NO CHANGE IN FUNCTIONALITY
issue.body:
**Motivation**: I wanted to fix some bugs with model generation, but needed to clarify things a bit beforehand

* reshuffled serializers templates in a separate directory, split the templates by schema type
* reindented model templates, using {{- }}, fixed some issues with template blank gobbling
* revamped docstring (fixed unattended line feed after comments, removed unused hardcoded reference)

* fixes #2215 (syntax error in templates, no more tolerated by go1.14)
* contributes to forthcoming fixes for #2189 (serializers with defaults), #2220 (edge cases on polymorphic types)
* contributes to #673 (templates readability)

Signed-off-by: Frederic BIDON <fredbi@yahoo.com>

Adapted test expectations to slight modifications of how goformat ends up when some blank lines are removed

Signed-off-by: Frederic BIDON <fredbi@yahoo.com>

Regenerated examples

Signed-off-by: Frederic BIDON <fredbi@yahoo.com>

body: Thanks, it solves the syntax error.

issue.title: Please make a new release for Go 1.14
issue.body:
## Problem statement

https://github.com/go-swagger/go-swagger/issues/2215 showed that go-swagger is broken for users of Go 1.14. There has not been a release since this was fixed. Any Go 1.14 users are forced to pin to a commit until a release is made.

Thanks!

body: Would it be possible to release this? :)

issue.title: harbor can not be build for users of Go 1.14 or 1.15

repository.name: harbor
repository.description: An open source trusted cloud native registry project that stores, signs, and scans content.

issue.body:
I built GO-swagger using Golang 1.15,Then execute the command "swagger generate server --template-dir=/root/test/harbor/tools/swagger/templates --exclude-main --additional-initialism=CVE --additional-initialism=GC -f api/v2.0/swagger.yaml -A harbor --target src/server/v2.0"

it show error information is as follows:

failed rendering template data for definition: template execution failed for template definition: template: schematype:2:18: executing "schemaType" at <(len .AllOf) gt 0>: can't give argument to non-function len .AllOf

This is because the GO is more stringent in grammar check after the 1.14 version, and the [Go-swagger fixes this issue in V0.23.0 version](https://github.com/go-swagger/go-swagger/issues/2215).,But harbor still use swagger v0.21.0 .So suggest to upgrade the Go-swagger version in Harbor to support Golang 1.14 or 1.15
